label.value: abolished protein-protein interaction during cellular response to hydrogen peroxide

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the binding of one protein to another does not occur during a cellular response to hydrogen peroxide. The relevant proteins may include the one encoded by the mutated gene, or may both be encoded by different genes.

definition.value: This term can be used for any protein-protein interaction that is affected by a mutation, whether or not the mutated gene product is one of the interacting proteins. We recommend noting which proteins were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abnormal protein localization to mitochondrion

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the mitochondrion is abnormal.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abolished protein localization to mitochondrion

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the mitochondrion does not occur.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abolished cell population growth on ethanol carbon source

value.value: A vegetative cell population growth phenotype in which a cell population does not grow in a medium containing ethanol as the carbon source.

definition.value: Use this term for a population of cells that does not grow with ethanol as the carbon source, but does grow using a different carbon source (a cell population that does not grow on any media would be considered inviable). Note that cell growth terms refer to growth under aerobic conditions unless stated otherwise.

label.value: decreased protein localization to nucleus during cellular response to hydrogen peroxide

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the nucleus is decreased during a cellular response to hydrogen peroxide.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abnormal mitochondrial fission

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which mitochondrial fission, the division of a mitochondrion into two or more separate compartments, is abnormal.

label.value: delayed onset of mitochondrial fission during cellular response to hydrogen peroxide

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which mitochondrial fission, the division of a mitochondrion into two or more separate compartments, begins later than normal during a cellular response to hydrogen peroxide.

label.value: increased LTR-derived RNA level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of any RNA transcribed from long terminal repeat elements (LTRs) measured in a cell is higher than normal.

definition.value: Consider annotating to a term describing abnormal transcription or abnormal regulation of transcription, but note that changes in RNA levels may result from changes in RNA stability as well as changes in transcription. We recommend noting which RNA(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: increased wtf-derived RNA level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of any RNA transcribed from wtf elements measured in a cell is higher than normal.

definition.value: Consider annotating to a term describing abnormal transcription or abnormal regulation of transcription, but note that changes in RNA levels may result from changes in RNA stability as well as changes in transcription. We recommend noting which RNA(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: increased viability upon nitrogen starvation

value.value: A cell population phenotype in which a larger than normal proportion of cells in the population remains viable when cells the population are subject to nitrogen starvation.

label.value: decreased protein localization to chromatin at long terminal repeat

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to chromatin at long terminal repeats is decreased.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased protein localization to chromatin at ncRNA genes

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to chromatin at non-coding RNA genes is decreased.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: increased histone H3-K9 acetylation at protein coding gene during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which acetylation of lysine at position 9 of histone H3 occurs to a greater extent than normal in regions containing protein-coding genes.

label.value: normal growth on methylglyoxal

value.value: A phenotype in which vegetative cell population growth is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) in a medium containing methylglyoxal.

label.value: decreased RNA level during cellular response to methylglyoxal

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of RNA measured in a cell during a cellular response to methylglyoxal is lower than normal. Total RNA or a specific RNA may be affected.

definition.value: Consider annotating to a term describing abnormal transcription or abnormal regulation of transcription, but note that changes in RNA levels may result from changes in RNA stability as well as changes in transcription. We recommend noting which RNA(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal RNA level during cellular response to methylglyoxal

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of RNA measured in a cell during a cellular response to methylglyoxal is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type). Total RNA or a specific RNA, such as the mRNA transcribed from a gene of interest, may be affected.

definition.value: We recommend noting which RNA(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: increased protein localization to nucleus during cellular response to methylglyoxal

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the nucleus is increased during a cellular response to methylglyoxal.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased protein localization to nucleus during cellular response to methylglyoxal

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the nucleus is decreased during a cellular response to methylglyoxal.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: increased protein phosphorylation during mitotic S phase

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the phosphorylation of one or more specific proteins, or of specific protein sites, occurs to a greater extent than normal during S phase of the mitotic cell cycle.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: increased protein phosphorylation during mitotic G1 phase

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the phosphorylation of one or more specific proteins, or of specific protein sites, occurs to a greater extent than normal during G1 phase of the mitotic cell cycle.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: increased protein phosphorylation during mitosis

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the phosphorylation of one or more specific proteins, or of specific protein sites, occurs to a greater extent than normal during mitosis.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: increased protein localization to nucleolus

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the nucleolus is increased.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased protein phosphorylation during mitosis

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the phosphorylation of one or more specific proteins, or of specific protein sites, occurs to a lower extent than normal during mitosis.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: increased protein phosphatase activity during mitosis

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of a protein phosphatase activity is increased during mitosis.

label.value: abolished mitotic cell cycle DNA replication checkpoint

value.value: A cell cycle checkpoint phenotype in which cell cycle regulation mediated by the mitotic cell cycle DNA replication checkpoint does not occur under conditions that normally trigger the checkpoint signaling and response. The DNA replication checkpoint normally prevents the initiation of mitosis until DNA replication is complete.

label.value: decreased duration of mitotic cell cycle DNA replication checkpoint

value.value: A cell cycle checkpoint phenotype in which the duration of mitotic cell cycle arrest or delay due to regulation by the DNA replication checkpoint is shorter than normal. The DNA replication checkpoint normally prevents the initiation of mitosis until DNA replication is complete.

label.value: meiotic cell cycle entry and sporulation in haploid during nitrogen starvation

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which haploid cells undergo meiotic nuclear division and attempt to sporulate when the cells are subject to nitrogen starvation. Haploid meiosis often results in the formation of a structure that resembles an azygotic ascus. Spores produced from a haploid cell have poor viability and appear to contain only 1/2C DNA on average.

label.value: increased protein localization to old growing cell tip

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to an old growing cell tip is increased.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: altered level of stress responsive gene mRNA during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of one or more messenger RNAs that are normally expressed during a cellular response to stress measured in a cell differs from normal (i.e. is higher or lower than observed in wild-type cells during vegetative growth).

definition.value: Consider annotating to a term describing abnormal transcription or abnormal regulation of transcription, but note that changes in RNA levels may result from changes in RNA stability as well as changes in transcription.

label.value: abnormal dioxygenase activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of a dioxygenase activity is abnormal.

label.value: abolished dioxygenase activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which a dioxygenase activity is absent.

label.value: syntelic kinetochore attachment during mitosis

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which the attachment of spindle microtubules to the kinetochore during a mitotic nuclear division results in the connection of both sister kinetochores to microtubules from the same spindle pole.

definition.value: Syntelic attachment activates the spindle assembly checkpoint, presumably due to lack of tension between the sister chromatids. If uncorrected, syntelic attachment will result in segregation of both sister chromatids to the same daughter cell, generating aneuploidy.

label.value: normal mitotic spindle assembly

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which assembly of the mitotic spindle is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type). Spindle assembly is the aggregation, arrangement and bonding together of a set of components to form the spindle.

label.value: normal growth on arsenic

value.value: A phenotype in which vegetative cell population growth is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) in a medium containing an arsenic-containing substance.

label.value: decreased vacuolar phytochelatin level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of phytochelatin measured in the vacuole is lower than normal.

label.value: decreased cadmium ion import into vacuole

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the import of cadmium ions into the vacuole occurs to a lower extent than normal.

label.value: decreased duration of S-phase DNA damage checkpoint

value.value: A cell cycle checkpoint phenotype in which the duration of cell cycle arrest or delay due to regulation by the S-phase DNA damage checkpoint is lower than in wild type.

label.value: decreased response to mitotic G2 DNA damage checkpoint signaling

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which a mitotic cell cycle arrest that normally occurs in response to the mitotic G2 DNA damage checkpoint is decreased. The mitotic G2 DNA damage checkpoint negatively regulates progression through the G2/M transition of the mitotic cell cycle in response to DNA damage. In a mutant, the checkpoint may fail to arrest or delay cell cycle progression under appropriate conditions, or the incidence or duration of arrest or delay may differ from wild type under any specified set of conditions.

label.value: abnormal mitotic G2 DNA damage checkpoint

value.value: A cell cycle checkpoint phenotype in which the mitotic G2 DNA damage checkpoint is abnormal. The mitotic G2 DNA damage checkpoint negatively regulates progression through the G2/M transition of the mitotic cell cycle in response to DNA damage. In a mutant, the checkpoint may fail to arrest or delay cell cycle progression under appropriate conditions, or the incidence or duration of arrest or delay may differ from wild type under any specified set of conditions.

label.value: abolished protein localization to cytoplasm during glucose starvation

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the localization of a protein to the cytoplasm is abolished when the cell is subject to glucose starvation.

definition.value: Note that FYPO uses "glucose starvation" to refer specifically to conditions in which glucose is scarce enough to trigger mating, meiosis, and sporulation. For phenotypes observed in the presence of enough glucose to prevent cells from mating, use a term that specifies "during vegetative growth" plus a condition to indicate low glucose. We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: sensitive to Ku-0063794

value.value: A phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells show increased sensitivity to Ku-0063794. Cells stop growing (and may die) at a concentration of Ku-0063794 that allows wild type cells to grow.

label.value: increased chromatin silencing at silent mating-type cassette

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which chromatin silencing at the silent mating-type cassettes is increased.

definition.value: Chromatin silencing phenotypes may reflect the assembly or maintenance of heterochromatin. See the GO cellular component term 'heterochromatin' (GO:0000792), and the biological process term 'heterochromatin organization' (GO:0070828).

label.value: increased protein localization to heterochromatin at silent mating-type cassette

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to heterochromatin at the silenced mating-type cassettes is increased.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal protein localization to heterochromatin at silent mating-type cassette

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to heterochromatin at the silenced mating-type cassettes is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: increased protein localization to pericentric heterochromatin during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to heterochromatin in pericentric regions is increased.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: merotelic kinetochore attachment during mitosis

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which the attachment of spindle microtubules to the kinetochore during a mitotic nuclear division results in the connection of a single kinetochore to both spindle poles.

label.value: meroterically attached lagging mitotic chromosomes

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which a single kinetochore becomes attached to both spindle poles, and sister chromatids do not move towards the spindle poles at the same time during mitosis prior to completion of chromosome segregation.

label.value: premature protein localization to mitotic spindle

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the mitotic spindle begins earlier than normal.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal single-stranded DNA binding

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which occurrence of single-stranded DNA binding by a gene product is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type). The relevant gene product may be encoded by the mutated gene, or by a different gene.

label.value: decreased single-stranded DNA binding

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which occurrence of single-stranded DNA binding by a gene product is decreased, when a gene or the bound DNA sequence is mutated. The affected gene product may be encoded by the mutated gene, or by a different gene.
